This is a missed-optimization in InstructionSimplify.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define i64 @ptrtoint_gep_sub(ptr %ptr, i64 %end.addr) {
  %ptr.addr = ptrtoint ptr %ptr to i64
  %size = sub i64 %end.addr, %ptr.addr
  %end = getelementptr i8, ptr %ptr, i64 %size
  %end.addr2 = ptrtoint ptr %end to i64
  ret i64 %end.addr2
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define i64 @ptrtoint_gep_sub(ptr %ptr, i64 %end.addr) {
  ret i64 %end.addr
}

```
